  "title": "Core Concepts of Getting Started with AWS in Practice",
  "lessonText": "This section explores the fundamental concepts of AWS and cloud computing.",
  "data": {
    "content": "• **Cloud Computing**: The delivery of computing services over the internet, enabling flexible resources.\n• **AWS Services**: A diverse range of services including computing, storage, and databases, tailored to meet various needs.\n• **Key Concepts**: Understanding terms like scalability, elasticity, and on-demand pricing is crucial for leveraging AWS effectively.\n• **Challenge**: Fill in the blanks using clues from the flashcards and video summary provided in this module. Identify key concepts of AWS and cloud computing.\n• **Quiz**: Test your understanding with questions such as:\n  - What is cloud computing?\n  - Which of the following best describes AWS services?"
  }
}
